    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Distinctive religious songs associated with African-American Christians of the southern United States; they were originally derived from African slaves having applied African musical elements to hymns that were ultimately European in origin.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
